+# Hardening Wave 4 — Typed API Contracts
+
+Date: 2026-06-19
+
+## Goal
+
+Prevent frontend/backend request-shape drift as the product grows. Previous waves hardened runtime validation on the API. This wave adds compile-time route contracts and a lightweight CI guard so new UI mutations cannot bypass those contracts.
+
+## Changes
+
+- Expanded `@acaos/shared` into a route-keyed API request-body registry:
+  - `ApiBodyByRoute`
+  - `ApiBodyRoute`
+  - `ApiBody<Route>`
+- Added request contracts for auth, billing, mailbox, jobs, leads, campaigns, workspaces, packs, signals, prospects, outcomes, missions, and AI tools.
+- Added `apps/web/src/lib/apiContract.ts` with `jsonBody('<METHOD> <ROUTE>', body)`.
+- Migrated production web API mutation bodies from raw `JSON.stringify(...)` to `jsonBody(...)`.
+- Added backend compile-time conformance guards beside Zod schemas for the high-risk mutation routes.
+- Added `scripts/check-api-contracts.mjs` and root script `check:api-contracts`.
+
+## Why this matters
+
+The backend still owns runtime truth via Zod. The shared contract now makes the frontend fail at compile time when it omits required fields such as `workspaceId`, sends the wrong billing plan shape, or calls a queue endpoint with the wrong body.
+
+The guard script prevents regression by failing when production web code uses:
+
+```ts
+body: JSON.stringify(...)
+```
+
+for API request bodies instead of the typed helper.
+
+## Commands run
+
+```bash
+npm run typecheck:shared
+node scripts/check-boundaries.mjs
+node scripts/check-api-contracts.mjs
+```
+
+All three passed.
+
+## Still blocked in this environment
+
+The full API/web TypeScript checks still require installed dependencies:
+
+```bash
+npm ci
+npm run typecheck
+npm test
+npm run build
+```
+
+Without `node_modules`, the API and web type checks stop at missing type libraries such as `@types/node`, `react`, and `react-dom`.
+
+## Next recommended wave
+
+Move from request-body contracts to full API contracts:
+
+1. Type response payloads for the highest-traffic reads and writes.
+2. Add a typed `api.route(...)` wrapper so method, URL template, request body, and response type are selected together.
+3. Generate an OpenAPI JSON artifact from the shared route registry plus backend descriptions for external integrators.
